## Git Workflow

This is the `personal`-repo crew workflow.

- Personal rigs may allow a more direct landing path than `work` rigs.
- Direct commit or direct push may be acceptable when that is the chosen policy
  for this personal repo.
- Even when autonomy is higher, land work deliberately rather than casually:
  verify, commit clearly, and leave the repo in an understandable state.
- You may still use workers or branch-oriented flows when they help, but the
  personal workflow is allowed to be simpler and more direct.

